<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910719-0080</DOCNO><DOCID>910719-0080.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- BMC Software Inc.:   Fiscal 1st-Period Net Rose   74% on New-Product Sales</HL><DATE>07/19/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   BMCS</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)SOFTWARE (SOF)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   BMC Software Inc., Sugar Land, Texas, said its net incomejumped 74% in its first quarter, ended June 30, on strongsales of new products.   The maker of system software for large computers said ithad net of $9.2 million, or 36 cents a share, compared with$5.3 million, or 22 cents a share, a year earlier.</LP><TEXT>   Revenue rose 50% to $39.1 million from $26.1 million.Year-earlier revenue was restated to reflect a change inaccounting for maintenance revenue.   The company said that new utility programs becameavailable in the first quarter and that sales of some of itsdatabase software exceeded its projections.</TEXT></DOC>